The color strength of the dyed fabrics was evaluated using a Konica-Minolta CM3610A spectrophotometer (illuminant D65, 10° standard observer). The measurement data provided the K/S, L*, a*, b* color coordinates which are lightness (L*), redness-greenness value (a*), yellowness-blueness value (b*). Consequently, to describe the depth of color on the textile substrate Kubelka-Munk theory was used (eq. 1). Using the equation (1) below, the K/S value was determined from reflectance values (R) measured for different wavelengths varying between 360 to 740 nm,1KS=(1−R)22R\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
